Package ohos.net

Class NetStatusCallback

  • java.lang.Object
    • ohos.net.NetStatusCallback

  • public class NetStatusCallback
extends Object
    Provides interfaces to listen for status changes of data networks.

    You can register a child class that inherits this class to listen for status changes of data networks.

    1

      • onBlockedStatusChanged

        public void onBlockedStatusChanged​(NetHandle handle,
                                   boolean blocked)
        A callback method used to notify applications of network congestion status changes.
        Parameters:
        handle - Indicates the NetHandle object whose congestion status has changed.
        blocked - Specifies whether the network is congested. The value true indicates that the network is congested, and the value false indicates that the network is not congested.
        Since:
        1

      • onLosing

        public void onLosing​(NetHandle handle,
                     long maxMsToLive)
        A callback method used to notify applications when a network disconnection is ongoing.
        Parameters:
        handle - Indicates the NetHandle object that is undergoing a disconnection.
        maxMsToLive - Indicates the time remaining before the network becomes unavailable.
        Since:
        1

      • onLost

        public void onLost​(NetHandle handle)
        Notifies applications of a serious network interruption or a normal network disconnection.

        Since:

      • onUnavailable

        public void onUnavailable​()
        Notifies applications of a failure to set up a network connection if no connection is set up before the NetManager.setupSpecificNet(ohos.net.NetSpecifier, ohos.net.NetStatusCallback) request times out.
        Since:
